Data sources let you fetch read-only information from external systems or existing infrastructure without managing that infrastructure in your config.

Syntax:
```hcl
data "<PROVIDER>_<TYPE>" "<LOCAL_NAME>" {
  filter_argument = value
}
```

Common DE data source patterns:

1. Fetch existing VPC (created by networking team):
```hcl
data "aws_vpc" "main" {
  tags = { Name = "production-vpc" }
}

resource "aws_db_subnet_group" "rds" {
  subnet_ids = data.aws_vpc.main.private_subnets
}
```

2. Fetch latest Amazon Linux AMI for EMR:
```hcl
data "aws_ami" "amazon_linux" {
  most_recent = true
  owners      = ["amazon"]
  filter {
    name   = "name"
    values = ["amzn2-ami-hvm-*-x86_64-gp2"]
  }
}
```

3. Fetch secret from AWS Secrets Manager:
```hcl
data "aws_secretsmanager_secret_version" "db_password" {
  secret_id = "prod/airflow/db_password"
}

# Use as: data.aws_secretsmanager_secret_version.db_password.secret_string
```

Data sources do NOT create resources. They only read. Perfect for referencing infrastructure owned by another team or another Terraform state.
